            <pb n="1"/>

            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Chicago</placeName>
                <date>April 12th AM 5626</date></p>
            <p>Reverend Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Having been a<lb/> constant reader of your widely<lb/> circulated and valuable
                journal<lb/> for the last five years and also<lb/> an admirer of your elaborate
                and<lb/> well timed articles in <sic>defence</sic><lb/> of the Orthodox principles
                of our<lb/> Holy religion I feel confident that<lb/>
                <sic>that</sic> I can appeal to you for<lb/> your kind assistance on my<lb/> own
                behalf. I am a native<lb/> of <placeName>London</placeName> my father is a<lb/>
                <add>Hebrew</add> there by sanction of <persName>Dr<lb/> Adler</persName> and have myself performed<lb/>
                the same office on various occasions<lb/> I immigrated from <placeName>London</placeName> about<lb/> eight
                months ago for the purpose<lb/> of my position in life being<lb/> bettered but found
                my hopes </p>

            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>were not to be realized owing<lb/> to the indifference entertained<lb/> towards our
                Religion by our people<lb/> You dear Sir may know of a<lb/> situation for
                    <add>Hebrew</add> and Hebrew and<lb/> English teacher in some strictly
                orthodox<lb/> congregation I apply to you on<lb/> account of you being the
                editor<lb/> of the leading orthodox organ of<lb/> this country. Your kind help<lb/>
                on my behalf will ever be<lb/> <sic>remmembered</sic> by<lb/> Your Obedient<lb/> Servant<lb/>
                <add>Hebrew</add><lb/>
                <persName role="author">Joseph A Cohen</persName><lb/> 311 Division Street<lb/>
                <placeName>Chicago Ill</placeName></p>
            <p><add>Hebrew</add></p>


        </body>
